"Costard F., Gautier E., Brunstein D., Hammadi J., Fedorov A., Yang D., Dupeyrat L.","Impact of the global warming on the fluvial thermal erosion over the Lena River in Central Siberia",2007,"Geophysical Research Letters","34","14", L14501,"","",,,10.1029/2007GL030212,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34548600068&partnerID=40&md5=bc23245bbdf90cc73945058e49cb8bc7","UMR 8148 IDES CNRS-UPS, Université Paris-Sud 11, F-91405 Orsay, France; University of Paris 8, CNRS, Laboratoire de Géographie Physique, F-93526 Meudon, France; Permafrost Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences, 677010 Yakutsk, Russian Federation; Water and Environment Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States","Costard, F., UMR 8148 IDES CNRS-UPS, Université Paris-Sud 11, F-91405 Orsay, France; Gautier, E., University of Paris 8, CNRS, Laboratoire de Géographie Physique, F-93526 Meudon, France; Brunstein, D., University of Paris 8, CNRS, Laboratoire de Géographie Physique, F-93526 Meudon, France; Hammadi, J., University of Paris 8, CNRS, Laboratoire de Géographie Physique, F-93526 Meudon, France; Fedorov, A., Permafrost Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences, 677010 Yakutsk, Russian Federation; Yang, D., Water and Environment Research Center, University of Alaska Fairbanks, Fairbanks, AK 99775, United States; Dupeyrat, L., UMR 8148 IDES CNRS-UPS, Université Paris-Sud 11, F-91405 Orsay, France","The hydrology of the Lena and its tributaries is characterized by an extremely episodic flow regime. Here we report recent climatic change in Central Siberia, and its impact on the fluvial thermal erosion. We point out three major changes since the 1980s: a marked reduction of the river ice thickness in winter, a pronounced increase of the water stream temperature in spring and a slight increase of the discharge during the break up (May-June). A GIS analysis based on aerial pictures and satellite images highlights the impact of the water warming on the frozen banks. The vegetated islands appear to be very sensitive to the water temperature increase, showing an acceleration of their head retreat (+21-29%). This suggests that recent global warming directly affects the fluvial dynamics and the erosional process of one of the largest arctic fluvial system. Copyright 2007 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Discharge (fluid mechanics); Geographic information systems; Hydrology; Rivers; Satellite imagery; Fluvial dynamics; Thermal erosion; Global warming; climate effect; discharge; erosion; fluvial process; GIS; global warming; ice thickness; river; satellite imagery; water temperature; Eurasia; Lena River; Russian Federation; Siberia",,,,,,"Antonov, S., Delta reki Leny (1960) Tr. Okeanogr. Kom. Akad. Nauk. SSSR, 6, pp. 25-34; Are, F.E., Thermal abrasion on coasts (1983) Proceedings of the Fourth International Conference on Permafrost, pp. 24-28. , Natl. Acad. Press, Washington, D. C; Beltaos, S. and B. C. Burrell (2002), Suspended sediments concentrations during the spring breakup of river ice, in Proceedings of the 14th IAHR Ice Symposium, 27-31 July 1998, Postdam, N. Y., 2, Ice in Surface Waters, edited by H. T. Shen, pp. 793-800, A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, NetherlandsBillfalk, L. (1982), Breakup of solid ice covers due to rapid water level variations, CRREL Rep. 82-3, Cold Reg. Res. and Eng. Lab., Hanover, N. HCustard, F., Dupeyrat, L., Gautier, E., Carey-Gailhardis, E., Fluvial thermal erosion investigations along a rapidly eroding river bank: Application to the Lena River (central Yakutia) (2003) Earth Surf. Processes Landforms, 28, pp. 1349-1359; Fedorov, A., Konstantinov, P., Observations of surface dynamics with thermokarst initiation, Yukechi site, central Yakutia (2003) Permafrost, 1, pp. 239-243. , edited by M. Philips, S. Springman, and L. U. Arenson, pp, A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, Netherlands; Gautier, E., Costard, F., Les systèmes fluviaux à chenaux anastomosés en milieu périglaciaire: La Léna et ses principaux affluents en Sibérie Centrale (2000) Geogr. Phys. Quat, 54, pp. 327-342; Gautier, E., Brunstein, D., Costard, F., Lodina, R., Fluvial dynamics in a deep permafrost zone: The case of the middle Lena River (central Yakutia) (2003) Permafrost, 1, pp. 271-275. , edited by M. Philips, S. Springman, and L. U. Arenson, pp, A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, Netherlands; Gordeev, V.V., Sidorov, I.S., Concentrations of major elements and their outflow into the Laptev Sea by the Lena River (1993) Mar. Chem, 43, pp. 33-45; Jahn, A., (1975) Problems of the Periglacial Zone, , 223 pp, Pol. Sci, Warsaw; Liu, B., Yang, D., Ye, B., Berezovskaya, S., Long-term open-water season stream temperature variations and changes over Lena River Basin in Siberia (2005) Global Planet. Change, 48, pp. 96-111; Pavlov, A.V., Current change of climate and permafrost in the Arctic and Sub-Arctic of Russia (1994) Permafrost Periglacial Processes, 5, pp. 101-110; Peterson, B.J., Holmes, R.M., McClelland, J.W., Vörösmarty, C.J., Lammers, R.B., Shiklomanov, A.I., Shiklomanov, I.A., Rahmstorf, S., Increasing river discharge to the Arctic Ocean (2002) Nature, 298, pp. 2171-2173; Randriamazaoro, R., Dupeyrat, L., Costard, F., Carey-Gailhardis, E., Fluvial thermal erosion: Heat balance integral method (2007) Earth Surf. Processes Landforms, , in press; Shen, H.T., Research on river ice processes: Progress and missing links (2003) J. Cold Reg. Eng, 17, pp. 135-142; Walker, H.J., Erosion in a permafrost dominated delta (1983) Proceedings of the Fourth International Conference on Permafrost, pp. 1344-1349. , Natl. Acad. Press, Washington, D. C; Walker, H.J., Hudson, P.F., Hydrologic and geomorphic processes in the Colville Delta, Alaska (2003) Geomorphology, 56, pp. 291-304; Yang, D., Kane, D.L., Hinzman, L.D., Zhang, X., Zhang, T., Ye, H., Siberian Lena River hydrologic regime and recent change (2002) J. Geophys. Res, 107 (D23), p. 4694. , doi:10.1029/2002JD002542; Yang, D., Ye, B., Kane, D.L., Streamflow changes 